 NEW DELHI Wed Oct 3,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The government will review a limit on market stabilisation scheme (MSS) bonds if there is a request from the central bank, Finance Minister Palaniappan Chidambaram said on Wednesday. "If there is a request from the Reserve Bank of India, we will certainly review it," Chidambaram told reporters when asked whether the government was contemplating raising the MSS ceiling. The RBI has stepped up selling MSS bonds as efforts to cap the local currency's gains following bold rate cuts by the US Federal Reserve released rupees into the system. Outstanding MSS issues stood at 1.176 trillion rupees ($29.5 billion rupees) as of Sept. 21, central bank data showed. It sold 100 billion rupees of these bonds last week. The current MSS limit is 1.5 trillion rupees and the cap has to be raised if outstanding issues exceed 1.35 trillion rupe
